# DocMind AI 🧠

> An intelligent document assistant powered by Claude AI — 
> upload PDFs, ask questions, get cited answers in real time.

[![Live Demo](https://img.shields.io/badge/Live%20Demo-docmind--ebon.vercel.app-blue)](https://docmind-ebon.vercel.app)
[![Backend](https://img.shields.io/badge/Backend-Railway-purple)](https://docmind-production.up.railway.app)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)](LICENSE)

![DocMind Demo](demo.gif)

---

## ✨ Features

**Core AI**
- 🔍 RAG-based document Q&A with source page citations
- ⚡ Real-time streaming responses (typewriter effect)
- 📚 Multi-document upload and cross-document search
- 💬 Persistent chat history per user per document

**Authentication**
- 🔐 JWT-based email/password auth
- 🔵 Google OAuth (one-click sign in)
- 🟦 Microsoft OAuth (one-click sign in)

**User Experience**
- 📄 PDF preview with View Full Page and Download
- 🌓 Dark/Light mode toggle with persistence
- 🗂️ Library and Recent tabs for document management
- 🔎 Real-time document name search
- 📱 Drag and drop upload with progress bar
- 🕐 Chat history restored after logout/login

**Production**
- 🚀 Backend deployed on Railway
- 🌐 Frontend deployed on Vercel
- 🗄️ SQLite database with SQLAlchemy ORM
- 🔒 Secure password hashing with PBKDF2

---

## 🏗️ Architecture
```
User → React Frontend (Vercel)
          ↓
     FastAPI Backend (Railway)
          ↓              ↓
     ChromaDB        SQLite DB
   (embeddings)   (users + chats)
          ↓
     Claude API
    (AI answers)
```

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | React, TypeScript, Vite | UI |
| Backend | Python, FastAPI | REST API |
| AI | Anthropic Claude API | Answer generation |
| Vector DB | ChromaDB | Semantic search |
| Database | SQLite + SQLAlchemy | Users + chat history |
| Auth | JWT + Google/Microsoft OAuth | Authentication |
| PDF | PyMuPDF | Text extraction |
| Deployment | Railway + Vercel | Production hosting |

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.11+
- Node.js 18+
- Anthropic API key

### Backend Setup
```bash
cd backend
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Create `backend/.env`:
```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_key_here
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
```

Start backend:
```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

### Frontend Setup
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
```

Create `frontend/.env`:
```
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
VITE_MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=your_microsoft_client_id
```

Start frontend:
```bash
npm run dev
```

Visit `http://localhost:5173`

---

## 🔑 Environment Variables

### Backend (`backend/.env`)
| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| ANTHROPIC_API_KEY | ✅ | Claude API key |
| GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID | ✅ | Google OAuth client ID |

### Frontend (`frontend/.env`)
| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID | ✅ | Google OAuth client ID |
| VITE_MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID | ✅ | Microsoft OAuth client ID |

---

## 📦 Deployment

### Backend → Railway
1. Connect GitHub repo to Railway
2. Set root directory to `backend`
3. Add environment variables in Railway dashboard
4. Deploy

### Frontend → Vercel
1. Connect GitHub repo to Vercel
2. Set root directory to `frontend`
3. Add environment variables in Vercel dashboard
4. Deploy

